{"type":"message","id":"c01b0810","parentId":"869f7578","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:43:25.710Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The \"Something went wrong\" error is not in OpenClaw's own code. It might be a Feishu channel-level error message when a message fails to send. Let me check the Feishu channel rules skill, or the openclaw-lark extension for message error handling.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The \"Something went wrong\" error typically appears when:\n1. A Feishu message fails to send\n2. A tool call fails\n3. An agent crashes\n\nSince it seems to be a recurring issue, let me look at the recent sessions to see if there's a pattern. But more importantly, let me address HALEI's main question about making subagents remember things like the main agent does.\n\n\nThe core issue is that subagents spawn with fresh sessions and don't inherit the conversation history or memory files. To fix this, I'd need to either spawn them as persistent sessions with `mode: \"session\"` so they maintain context, or inject relevant context at spawn time so they have the necessary information to work with.\n\nLooking at the main agent's memory layer—it has the vector store from lancedb, the file-based MEMORY.md and daily notes, plus the OpenViking context engine doing auto-recall. But when spawning a subagent, none of this gets passed along. The cleanest approach would be to modify the spawn configuration to include the necessary memory context, or ensure subagents use the same recall mechanisms. Let me check the session configuration to see what parameters control how context gets passed to subagents."},{"type":"text","text":"\"Something went wrong\" 没找到直接来源——不是 OpenClaw 代码里的报错，可能是飞书 channel 在消息发送失败时显示的通用错误。我继续查。\n\n现在重点解决**记忆问题**：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xb1kn41hyrs6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); agents=d.get('agents',{}); print(json.dumps(agents, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False))\" 2>/dev/null | head -60"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776159790186,"responseId":"062d3f2e5d4768eb3094d16a66f281ef"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e480e36b","parentId":"c01b0810","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:43:25.798Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xb1kn41hyrs6_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"defaults\": {\n    \"model\": {\n      \"primary\": \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"fallbacks\": [\n        \"gemini/gemini-1.5-flash\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"models\": {\n      \"openrouter/auto\": {\n        \"alias\": \"OpenRouter\"\n      },\n      \"openrouter/free\": {\n        \"alias\": \"free\"\n      },\n      \"gemini/gemini-1.5-flash\": {\n        \"alias\": \"gemini-1.5-flash\"\n      },\n      \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\": {\n        \"alias\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"workspace\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace\",\n    \"compaction\": {\n      \"mode\": \"safeguard\"\n    },\n    \"memorySearch\": {\n      \"provider\": \"gemini\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"list\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"main\",\n      \"agentDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main\",\n      \"model\": \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"subagents\": {\n        \"allowAgents\": [\n          \"*\"\n        ],\n        \"model\": {\n          \"primary\": \"gemini/gemini-1.5-flash\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"tools\": {\n        \"allow\": [\n          \"read\",\n          \"write\",\n          \"edit\",\n          \"apply_patch\",\n          \"exec\",\n          \"process\",\n          \"memory_search\",\n          \"memory_get\",\n          \"web_search\",\n          \"sessions_list\",\n          \"sessions_history\",\n          \"sessions_send\",\n          \"sessions_spawn\",\n          \"sessions_yield\",\n          \"subagents\","}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":50,"aggregated":"{\n  \"defaults\": {\n    \"model\": {\n      \"primary\": \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"fallbacks\": [\n        \"gemini/gemini-1.5-flash\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"models\": {\n      \"openrouter/auto\": {\n        \"alias\": \"OpenRouter\"\n      },\n      \"openrouter/free\": {\n        \"alias\": \"free\"\n      },\n      \"gemini/gemini-1.5-flash\": {\n        \"alias\": \"gemini-1.5-flash\"\n      },\n      \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\": {\n        \"alias\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"workspace\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace\",\n    \"compaction\": {\n      \"mode\": \"safeguard\"\n    },\n    \"memorySearch\": {\n      \"provider\": \"gemini\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"list\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"main\",\n      \"agentDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main\",\n      \"model\": \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"subagents\": {\n        \"allowAgents\": [\n          \"*\"\n        ],\n        \"model\": {\n          \"primary\": \"gemini/gemini-1.5-flash\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"tools\": {\n        \"allow\": [\n          \"read\",\n          \"write\",\n          \"edit\",\n          \"apply_patch\",\n          \"exec\",\n          \"process\",\n          \"memory_search\",\n          \"memory_get\",\n          \"web_search\",\n          \"sessions_list\",\n          \"sessions_history\",\n          \"sessions_send\",\n          \"sessions_spawn\",\n          \"sessions_yield\",\n          \"subagents\",","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776159805791}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b585d5c","parentId":"e480e36b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:43:46.891Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue clearly. Looking at the `subagents` config:\n\n```json\n\"subagents\": {\n  \"allowAgents\": [\"*\"],\n  \"model\": {\n    \"primary\": \"gemini/gemini-1.5-flash\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe subagents are using `gemini/gemini-1.5-flash` as their primary model, not MiniMax-M2.7. And they're using the default \"run\" mode which creates fresh sessions without memory.\n\nTo fix the memory issue for subagents, I need to configure them to:\n1. Use the same memory system as the main agent\n2. Use `mode: \"session\"` instead of `mode: \"run\"` for persistent sessions\n\nBut actually, looking at this more carefully - the subagents don't have their own memory files. The issue is that subagents spawned with `sessions_spawn` (run mode) don't get access to the workspace memory files unless explicitly configured.\n\nThe key insight is: the main agent (KIIT/me) uses:\n- `MEMORY.md` and `memory/*.md` files in workspace\n- `memory_search` tool to query them\n- OpenViking for context-level memory\n\nSubagents need to be configured to also use these memory mechanisms. The `memory_search` tool is already in the subagent tools allowlist, so they can use it. But they need to be instructed to do so at the start of their prompts.\n\nAlso, the `memory_search` in the main config uses `provider: \"gemini\"` which is the vector search. But the subagents also have their own `memory_search` tool available.\n\nThe real issue might be simpler: the subagents just aren't being told to use memory. Their prompts don't include the AGENTS.md SOUL.md context that tells them to read memory files at startup.\n\nLooking at the subagent spawning configuration, I don't see a `prompt` or `context` section that would inject the memory-reading behavior into subagent sessions.\n\n\nThe fix would likely involve configuring default agent settings so subagents automatically read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` and `MEMORY.md` at startup, switching them to persistent `mode: \"session\"` instead of one-shot `mode: \"run\"`, and potentially pointing them to the same vector search provider. I should also check the feishu-multi-agent-manager skill to see if it has relevant configuration guidance."},{"type":"text","text":"找到原因了。配置里 subagent 用的是 `gemini/gemini-1.5-flash`，而且是 **run 模式**（一次性），不持久。\n\n让我看看当前完整的 agent 配置，然后给出修改方案：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l4df1q5zhu7r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); agents=d.get('agents',{}); print(json.dumps(agents, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False))\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776159805800,"responseId":"062d3f3e44c539c5d3a00a62f8ac8dbf"}}
