{"type":"message","id":"09ba1419","parentId":"96db19e0","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:44:26.530Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The subagents config at the root level is empty. The subagent config is only inside `agents.list[0]` (the main agent). So the subagent settings are defined per-agent. I need to change the main agent's subagent config to use session mode.\n\nLet me check how subagents are spawned - the `sessions_spawn` call has a `mode` parameter that can be \"run\" or \"session\". The default appears to be \"run\". I need to change the default or change how they're spawned.\n\nActually, looking at the config more carefully:\n- The `agents.list[0].subagents` config controls what subagents the main agent can spawn\n- It has `allowAgents: [\"*\"]` and a `model` setting\n\n\n- But there's no default `mode` setting here\n\nThe `mode` is probably set at the `sessions_spawn` call site. Since I can't see the workspace files that contain those calls, the real fix might be to make the workspace memory files the source of truth instead - that way even run-mode subagents could reference them if they invoke memory_search at startup. Or I could just update the spawn calls to use `mode: \"session\"` instead of the default run mode."},{"type":"text","text":"需要找到 spawn 调用的位置，看现在用的是 `run` 还是 `session`：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dg6snospr2la_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"sessions_spawn\\|mode.*session\\|mode.*run\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".jsonl\\|node_modules\" | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776159855128,"responseId":"062d3f705e8339900f466f779047bc19"}}
