{"type":"message","id":"2cccdd87","parentId":"4fc4388d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:44:37.763Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_l1mhesi864dy_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// SessionContext 类型定义（由 OpenClaw 运行时提供）\ninterface SessionContext {\n  model?: {\n      model?: {\n        mode: string;\n2. 分派任务时使用 \\`sessions_spawn\\` 或 \\`sessions_send\\` 工具\n1. 使用 \\`sessions_send\\` 工具进行跨 Agent 通信\nasync function createMultipleAgents(ctx: SessionContext, agents: Array<{\n  model?: string;\n          ...(agent.model ? { model: { primary: agent.model } } : {}),\nexport async function main(ctx: SessionContext, args: Record<string, any>): Promise<void> {"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":24,"aggregated":"// SessionContext 类型定义（由 OpenClaw 运行时提供）\ninterface SessionContext {\n  model?: {\n      model?: {\n        mode: string;\n2. 分派任务时使用 \\`sessions_spawn\\` 或 \\`sessions_send\\` 工具\n1. 使用 \\`sessions_send\\` 工具进行跨 Agent 通信\nasync function createMultipleAgents(ctx: SessionContext, agents: Array<{\n  model?: string;\n          ...(agent.model ? { model: { primary: agent.model } } : {}),\nexport async function main(ctx: SessionContext, args: Record<string, any>): Promise<void> {","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776159877757}}
{"type":"message","id":"4139c6a7","parentId":"2cccdd87","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:44:49.988Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The feishu-multi-agent-manager creates agents but I don't see where it sets the session mode. Let me look at the actual spawn calls in the workspace to understand how agents are being spawned.\n\nActually, the real issue might be simpler. Let me look at how the main KIIT session spawns subagents. The issue is that every time KIIT calls `sessions_spawn`, it's using `mode: \"run\"` (one-shot) by default.\n\nBut looking at the sessions list, many of the subagents have very short runtimes (e.g., product-selector ran for ~2 minutes then ended). If they were session mode they'd be persistent.\n\nThe fix for \"memory\" would be:\n1. When spawning subagents, use `mode: \"session\"` instead of `mode: \"run\"`\n\n\n2. Give each subagent its own workspace with proper agent files so they can maintain context\n\nI should check the AGENTS.md file to see what the default spawn behavior is configured to."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1tuazmaknp0w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md 2>/dev/null | grep -A5 -i \"session\\|spawn\\|run\\|mode\" | head -40"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1tuazmaknp0w_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw/agents -name \"*.json\" -o -name \"*.yaml\" 2>/dev/null | head -10 && echo \"---\" && ls ~/.openclaw/agents/ 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776159877764,"responseId":"062d3f868b55f5aaf53e64a27fb22686"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5054f713","parentId":"4139c6a7","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:44:50.035Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1tuazmaknp0w_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n--\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Memory\n\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\n\n- **Daily notes:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create `memory/` if needed) — raw logs of what happened\n- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — your curated memories, like a human's long-term memory\n\nCapture what matters. Decisions, context, things to remember. Skip the secrets unless asked to keep them.\n--\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\n\n### 📝 Write It Down - No \"Mental Notes\"!\n--\n- \"Mental notes\" don't survive session restarts. Files do.\n- When someone says \"remember this\" → update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` or relevant file\n- When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, or the relevant skill\n- When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it\n- **Text > Brain** 📝"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":18,"aggregated":"## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n--\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Memory\n\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\n\n- **Daily notes:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create `memory/` if needed) — raw logs of what happened\n- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — your curated memories, like a human's long-term memory\n\nCapture what matters. Decisions, context, things to remember. Skip the secrets unless asked to keep them.\n--\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\n\n### 📝 Write It Down - No \"Mental Notes\"!\n--\n- \"Mental notes\" don't survive session restarts. Files do.\n- When someone says \"remember this\" → update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` or relevant file\n- When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, or the relevant skill\n- When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it\n- **Text > Brain** 📝","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776159890026}}
