{"type":"message","id":"3b02405e","parentId":"c8b9fa52","timestamp":"2026-04-14T09:59:26.670Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants clarity: each sub-agent should have its own isolated workspace directory under Workspace/, with its own SOUL.md, AGENTS.md, memory files, etc. But also, the selector agent should be able to remember things just like the main agent does.\n\nSo the key is: isolated workspace = independent files = memory is naturally independent.\n\nThe current `workspace-selector` already exists with its own memory, AGENTS.md, etc. I moved `tts` agent's workspaceDir to main workspace incorrectly - I should revert that.\n\nBut wait - the user is saying the selector should have its own isolated space AND be able to remember everything. The current `workspace-selector` already has its own memory folder. So if I just keep it as `workspace-selector` (renamed to `Selector`) and keep the agent's workspaceDir pointing to it, it should naturally remember things.\n \nI think I see the actual issue now - the tts agent was working fine with its own workspace, but I changed it to point to the main workspace and broke that isolation. I need to revert that change and make sure the selector agent stays in its own dedicated workspace so it can maintain its own memory and context independently."},{"type":"text","text":"明白了，逻辑很简单：\n\n> **隔离空间 = 独立文件 = 自然记住**\n\n`workspace-selector/` 已经有自己的 memory/、SOUL.md、AGENTS.md —— 只要保持隔离，它就会像你一样记住一切。\n\n我刚才把你 `tts` agent 的 workspaceDir 改到主目录是错的，需要还原：\n\n```\ntts/agent/config.json\nworkspaceDir: \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-selector\"  ← 改回这个\n```\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b9pi2tpmo3ag_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent/config.json","edits":[{"oldText":"\"workspaceDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace\",","newText":"\"workspaceDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-selector\","}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":