{"type":"message","id":"36854e63","parentId":"9283173b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:04:57.036Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Selector workspace already has:\n- AGENTS.md, BOOTSTRAP.md, HEARTBEAT.md, IDENTITY.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, USER.md - all the basic files\n- memory/ with historical records from April 9-14\n- skills/ with linkfox-echotik product search tools\n\nThe tts agent config is good - session mode, correct workspace.\n\nNow let me think about what \"选品Agent 能干活\" means. It needs to:\n1. Search products (linkfox-echotik already installed)\n2. Have access to 1688 product search (1688-product-search skill already installed)\n\n\n3. Access Google Trends (google-trends already installed)\n\nSo all the core skills are already there. The main blocker is that when I spawn it as a subagent, it needs to be able to actually use these skills - the tools like `feishu_bitable_app`, `feishu_sheet`, `linkfox_echotik_product_search`, `linkfox_echotik_new_product_rank`, and `1688_product_search` need to be accessible from the Selector workspace, not just present in the directory. be invoked as tools?\n\nLet me think about what might be wrong. The subagent spawns and:\n1. Asks what product category to analyze (shows it's fresh)\n2. Doesn't use the available skills/tools\n3. Has the tools but doesn't know when to call them\n\nThe issue might be that the `BOOTSTRAP.md` still exists in the Selector workspace, which would cause the agent to reinitialize on startup. But more likely, the real problem is that the agent isn't properly connecting to the skills that are already installed there. me check the Selector BOOTSTRAP.md:\n\nActually wait - the SOUL.md in Selector already has a role defined. The BOOTSTRAP.md might be interfering.\n\nLet me also look at whether the skills are properly callable. The tools allow list for tts agent is:\n- cron, read, write, edit, apply_patch, memory_search, memory_get, browser, message\n\nIt does NOT include web_search, web_fetch, exec... So the agent can't actually run web searches or use the skill tools directly. The skills are installed but the agent doesn't have permission to call them!\n\nThis is likely the core problem - the tools.allow list is too restrictive. The agent can't use the skills that are installed in its workspace because they're not in its tools allowlist.\n\nLooking at what skills are actually available: linkfox-echotik for product search, 1688-product-search, and google-trends for market research. The agent also needs Feishu integration to write results to bitable. But with the current allowlist, it can't execute any of these - the tools are there but inaccessible.\n\nI need to expand the tts agent's tools.allow to include web_search, web_fetch, exec, and the Feishu tools so it can actually leverage these capabilities."},{"type":"text","text":"环境已经很完整了，但有一个关键问题——**tts agent 的 tools allowlist 太窄，装了技能但叫不动**：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2fus70u50o03_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/Selector/skills/linkfox-echotik-product-search/ && echo \"---\" && ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/.agents/skills/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776161074247,"responseId":"062d44328070be66193ccbb57bbae466"}}
