{"type":"message","id":"fbd15600","parentId":"b32fdf36","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:06:20.588Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`sessions_spawn` with `mode=\"session\"` requires `thread=true`. This makes sense for Discord/Telegram threads. But since we're on Feishu, I need to figure out the right approach.\n\nActually, looking at the error - the session mode needs thread binding. This is for Discord/Telegram where thread is required. For Feishu, maybe I should use `mode=\"run\"` for now or figure out how to do thread binding on Feishu.\n\nWait - but the user wants persistent sessions. Let me think about this differently. The `spawnMode: \"session\"` in the agent config should handle this at the configuration level, not the spawn call level.\n \nI see the distinction now: `spawnMode` in the config controls the session persistence type (run vs session), while the `thread` parameter in `sessions_spawn` determines whether the subagent stays bound to a conversation thread. The error is telling me that for Feishu, I might not need thread binding at all, so I should try spawning without specifying `thread=true`."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qsta0yt4hv8j_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"你好，请做一个简单的自我介绍，说明你是谁，你的职责，以及你目前能记住什么。","label":"选品Agent-测试","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"tts","mode":"session","thread":true}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776161170489,"responseId":"062d4492d9ad9c18133ceb8a9bc3bc89"}}
