{"type":"message","id":"6b4b685a","parentId":"849aa488","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:06:42.102Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, `thread=true` is unavailable. This means the `spawnMode: \"session\"` we configured won't work in the current setup because there's no channel plugin that supports thread-bound subagent spawning.\n\nLet me try with `mode=\"run\"` but that would defeat the purpose. Let me think about what other options I have.\n\nActually, maybe I should try without `thread=true` but with `mode=\"session\"`. Let me check if there's an error message.\n\nWait, the first attempt returned error: `mode=\"session\" requires thread=true`. The second attempt with `thread=true` returned: `thread=true is unavailable because no channel plugin registered subagent_spawning hooks.`\n\n\nSo session mode fundamentally requires thread support that isn't available. Let me explore spawning directly with `runtime=\"acp\"` instead, which might offer different configuration options for the agent ID.\n\nThe real constraint here is memory - if session mode won't work without thread support, the subagent won't retain anything between calls anyway. Maybe I should try the spawn without specifying session mode at all, or experiment with the `lightContext` option to see if that changes the behavior. I'm realizing the core issue: `spawnMode: \"session\"` in the config doesn't actually work because `thread=true` isn't supported without the right channel hooks, and `runtime: \"subagent\"` defaults to `mode: \"run\"` which is one-shot. So that setting might be inert.\n\nFor persistent memory, I'd need either an ACP harness with thread support, or the subagent to actively write to and read from memory files—but the config shows `exec` isn't even in the tools list for `product-selector`, which severely limits what the agent can do.\n\nFor `tts` I just added `exec`, `web_search`, and `web_fetch`, but the sandbox still has restrictions. Looking at what actually changed: `tts` got `workspaceDir` redirected to Selector, the full tools list, and `spawnMode: \"session\"`. But if `spawnMode: \"session\"` can't actually run without thread support, then both agents are stuck with the same problem.\n\nI should try spawning a subagent without session mode and see if memory_search works—that's what would actually tell me if recall is possible. Or I could try the ACP runtime with the feishu channel to see if that bypasses the thread limitation."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p0kyqcdlrkds_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"你好，请做一个简单的自我介绍，说明你是谁，你的职责，以及你目前能记住什么。同时请读取 Selector/skills/linkfox-echotik-product-search/SKILL.md 的前20行，看看skill是否能正常访问。","label":"选品Agent-测试","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"tts","mode":"run"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776161180835,"responseId":"062d449d3aa75026281799d8f855d581"}}
