{"type":"message","id":"c796acf7","parentId":"a9218815","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:14:43.502Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-14 18:14:41 GMT+8] Feishu[kiit] DM | ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb [msg:om_x100b52d577cec8b4c36ffdf84933a34, reply_to:om_x100b52d4edb0a0bcb2744105dcaeef9]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b52d577cec8b4c36ffdf84933a34\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-14 18:14 GMT+8\",\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"body\": \"[message_id=om_x100b52d4edb0a0bcb2744105dcaeef9] <card>\\n搞清楚了，4.12 的记忆是**三层并存**：\\n\\n| 层 | 技术 | 存储位置 | 作用 |\\n|------|------|------|------|\\n| 文件记忆 | memory-core | MEMORY.md + memory/*.md | 人工维护的长期记忆 |\\n| 向量记忆 | memory-lancedb | ~/.openclaw/memory/lancedb-pro/ | 语义搜索（用 OpenAI embeddings 建索引） |\\n| 上下文引擎 | OpenViking | 远程服务 localhost:1933 | auto-recall/auto-capture，对话级上下文管理 |\\n|  |  |  |  |`memory_search` 工具会同时查 **lancedb 向量库** 和 **文件记忆** 两边。\\n\\nOpenViking 是作为独立 context-engine 插件接入的，跟前两层不一样——它管的是\\\"对话过程中实时 recall/capture\\\"。\\n\\n简单说：文件记忆是人工写的，向量记忆是自动索引的，OpenViking 是对话级别的上下文管道。三者各司其职。\\n</card>\"\n}\n```\n\n还是这个存储的问题，是不是要考虑，在新的4月12号的架构当中，OpenViking的存在还有必要吗？"}],"timestamp":1776161683490}}
{"type":"message","id":"37fa026f","parentId":"c796acf7","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:14:59.687Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether OpenViking is still necessary given the new 4.12 architecture. Let me think about this.\n\nFrom what we know:\n1. OpenViking runs as a plugin at localhost:1933\n2. It provides `auto-recall` (before_prompt_build) and `auto-capture` (afterTurn) and `assemble=archive+active`\n3. The `memory_search` tool searches both lancedb vector DB AND file memory\n4. OpenViking is registered as a \"context-engine\"\n\nThe question is: if we have:\n- File memory (memory-core + MEMORY.md + memory/*.md) - manual long-term\n\n\n- LanceDB vector memory - semantic search\n- The subagent's own session context\n\nIs OpenViking redundant? It seems like OpenViking is supposed to handle automatic memory management during conversation, but I'm not entirely sure what it's actually doing versus what memory_search already does. I should check what memory-lancedb is actually indexing and what the practical difference is between OpenViking's recall/capture functionality and the standard memory search approach.\n\nLooking at the status output showing \"0 files · 0 chunks\" in LanceDB, it seems like the vector database might not be populated yet. The real question is whether OpenViking's context engine adds unique value on top of what file memory and vector search already provide, or if it's solving a problem that doesn't actually exist in this setup. Let me think about what each layer actually does."},{"type":"text","text":"好问题。先查一下当前 OpenViking 的实际运行状态：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1tmoh07utj2w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:1933/health 2>/dev/null || curl -s http://localhost:1933/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1tmoh07utj2w_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; 