{"type":"message","id":"1df98d48","parentId":"10bc0c03","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:34:47.934Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether OpenClaw 4.12's default storage can satisfy the short/medium/long term memory needs. Let me think about this.\n\nBased on what we found:\n- memory-core: MEMORY.md + memory/*.md (file-based)\n- memory-lancedb: 0 chunks, empty\n- OpenViking: registered but not running\n\nSo the actual working storage is just the file-based memory-core. But OpenViking is registered as a context-engine and the status showed it registered hooks. However, since the remote service isn't running, those hooks probably do nothing.\n\nThe question is: can the default storage (memory-core) satisfy short/medium/long term memory needs?\n \nFor the Selector agent, we now have MEMORY.md for long-term strategic knowledge, daily memory files for medium-term context, and the current conversation for short-term. Since LanceDB and OpenViking aren't actually functioning, the system is relying entirely on file-based storage. While this approach is simpler and more reliable, the lack of vector search means we can't do semantic recall—we'd only be able to search by exact keyword matches.\n\nI should walk through what the default setup actually provides and whether it covers the three memory tiers, then suggest disabling the non-functional components like LanceDB and OpenViking to keep things clean."},{"type":"text","text":"是的，4.12 默认的 memory-core（纯文件）就能完整覆盖三层，而且更简单：\n\n| 层级 | 文件 | 实际效果 |\n|------|------|---------|\n| 短期 | 当前会话上下文 | ✅ 每次对话自动携带 |\n| 中期 | `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` | ✅ 每日记录 |\n| 长期 | `MEMORY.md` | ✅ 精选提炼 |\n\n**三段都靠文件，没有依赖，坏掉的风险最低。**\n\n之前看到的 lancedb（0 chunks）和 OpenViking（端口没监听）都是\"注册了但没干活\"的状态，反而是噪音。\n\n要不要我把这两个从配置里禁用掉，回复干净？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cache